As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 1,910 people, 589 households, and 436 families residing in the city.

In 2018 there was an estimated population of 1,887, a decrease of 273 inhabitants since the 2010 census.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=2018 ACS 5-Year Estimates Detailed Tables |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=B01003&tid=ACSDT5Y2018.B01003&layer=place&vintage=2018&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=0&mode= |access-date=2020-01-23 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> Per the [[American Community Survey]]'s 2018 estimates, a total of 598 households and 468 families resided in Waskom.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |title=2018 ACS Households and Families Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=S1101&tid=ACSST5Y2018.S1101&layer=place&vintage=2018&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=25&mode= |access-date=2020-01-25 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> There were 833 housing units in 2018.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |title=2018 ACS Demographic and Housting Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=DP05&tid=ACSDP5Y2018.DP05&layer=place&vintage=2018&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=24&mode= |access-date=2020-01-25 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> At the [[census]] of [[2010 United States Census|2010]] and the American Community Survey's estimates, there were 2,160 people, 732 households, and 460 families residing in the city.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=2010 ACS Demographic and Housting Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=DP05&tid=ACSDP5Y2010.DP05&layer=place&vintage=2010&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=24&mode= |access-date=2020-01-25 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=2010 ACS Households and Families Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=S1101&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101&layer=place&vintage=2010&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=25&mode= |access-date=2020-01-25 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> The population density was {{convert|750.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}} in 2000. There were 868 housing units in 2010.<ref name=":3" />

In 2000, there were 790 households, out of which 34.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 51.9% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 15.9% had a female householder with no husband present, and 27.6% were non-families. 24.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 10.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.62 and the average family size was 3.10.

In the city, the population was spread out, with 28.6% under the age of 18, 8.9% from 18 to 24, 26.6% from 25 to 44, 23.7% from 45 to 64, and 12.0% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 35 years. For every 100 females, there were 99.0 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 93.4 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $29,737, and the median income for a family was $32,243. Males had a median income of $29,625 versus $18,859 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $13,080. About 19.4% of families and 24.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 35.5% of those under age 18 and 14.8% of those age 65 or over.

In 2018, 48.1% of households had children under the age of 18 living with them.<ref name=":4" /> The average household size was 3.16 and the average family size was 3.59.<ref name=":4" /> The median age of Waskom was 49.9.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2018 ACS Age and Sex Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=S0101&tid=ACSST5Y2018.S0101&layer=place&vintage=2018&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=23&mode= |access-date=2020-01-25 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> The median income was $29,844.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2018 ACS Annual Income Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Waskom%20city,%20Texas&g=1600000US4876636&table=S1901&tid=ACSST5Y2018.S1901&layer=place&vintage=2018&cid=DP05_0001E&lastDisplayedRow=16&mode= |access-date=2020-01-25 |website=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref> In 2020 the average rent for a two-bedroom apartment was $799 according to [[Sperling's BestPlaces]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=Cost of Living Estimates for Waskom, Texas|url=https://www.bestplaces.net/cost_of_living/city/texas/waskom|website=Sperling's BestPlaces}}</ref> making it relatively cheaper than neighboring Shreveport, Louisiana.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Cost of Living Estimates for Shreveport, Louisiana|url=https://www.bestplaces.net/cost_of_living/city/louisiana/shreveport|website=Sperling's BestPlaces}}</ref>

