At the 2020 census, its racial composition was 57.02% non-Hispanic white, 13.04% Black or African American, 0.63% Native American or Alaska Native, 0.31% Asian, 0.1% some other race, 4.45% multiracial, and 24.25% Hispanic or Latino of any race.<ref name=":7" /> The racial makeup in 2018 was 61.0% [[Non-Hispanic whites|non-Hispanic white]], 17.1% [[African Americans|Black or African American]], 0.7% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American or Alaskan Native]], and 2.2% from [[Multiracial Americans|two or more races]].<ref name=":5" /> [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanics or Latinos]] of any race were 19.0% of the city's populace.<ref name=":5" /> The [[2010 United States census|2010 U.S. census]] determined Waskom's population was 69.77% White, 13.29% Black or African American, 0.93% Native American or Alaska Native, 2.22% two or more races, 13.56% some other race, 0.23% Asian, and 19.58% Hispanic or Latino of any race.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Waskom, TX Population - Census 2010 and 2000 Interactive Map, Demographics, Statistics, Quick Facts - CensusViewer|url=http://censusviewer.com/city/TX/Waskom|url-status=usurped|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220135224/http://censusviewer.com/city/TX/Waskom|archive-date=February 20, 2020|access-date=2020-12-17|website=censusviewer.com}}</ref> In 2000, the racial makeup of the city was 75.05% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 15.76% [[African American (U.S. Census)|Black or African American]], 0.63% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.15% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 7.16% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.26% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino (ethnic categories)|Hispanic and Latin Americans]] of any race were 9.86% of the population.

===Religion===
Waskom and Harrison County are predominantly Christian areas, typical of the [[Bible Belt]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Religion in Waskom, Texas|url=https://www.bestplaces.net/religion/city/tx/waskom|website=Sperling's BestPlaces}}</ref> The largest Christian tradition in the city of Waskom are the [[Baptists]], followed by [[Methodism|Methodists]] and [[Catholic Church|Catholics]]. Of the Baptist population, the largest denomination is the [[Southern Baptist Convention]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=SBC Churches Directory|url=https://churches.sbc.net/|access-date=2020-12-17|website=churches.sbc.net|language=en-US}}</ref> Predominantly African American-led Baptist churches are either [[independent Baptist]], or part of the National Baptist Convention ([[National Baptist Convention, USA, Inc.|USA]] or [[National Baptist Convention of America International, Inc.|America]]). There is one [[United Methodist Church|United Methodist]] congregation in the city limits,<ref>{{Cite web|title=Search - Find A Church|url=https://www.umc.org/en/find-a-church/search|access-date=2020-12-17|website=The United Methodist Church|language=en|archive-date=April 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413050031/https://www.umc.org/en/find-a-church/search|url-status=dead}}</ref> and one Catholic church.<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Best Catholic Churches in Waskom, Texas, United States Rated By Past Visitors|url=https://www.catholicdirectory.com/united-states/texas/waskom|access-date=2020-12-17|website=The Catholic Directory|language=en}}</ref>

